  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel Piccola Vela's been a favourite with our guests for many years. The service here is great and you’re always greeted with a smile. The hotel used to be a private villa and it’s tucked away from the road, with a large driveway leading up to the porch. There’s a pool in the gardens, which is a lovely place to relax when it’s sunny. If you get too hot, head for a shady spot under the olive trees. The restaurant terrace is right next to the pool so you won’t have to venture far for lunch. Around the back of the hotel there's a pretty lemon garden and a small heated pool. There’s also a small spa if you want to have a day of relaxion!</p>
<p>The hotel’s very close to the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/574a76e62f8b4388af2fd61b34c7ed1b" href="/{localLink:umb://document/574a76e62f8b4388af2fd61b34c7ed1b}" title="Desenzano">Desenzano</a>. You can walk to the lake in around ten minutes and there are bars and restaurants just a few minutes away. The train station's also close, so day trips to nearby cities like <a data-udi="umb://document/201893063f65496384a9bd17846543a7" href="/{localLink:umb://document/201893063f65496384a9bd17846543a7}" title="Venice">Venice</a> and <a data-udi="umb://document/41229767036d47f28a27ac846e23458b" href="/{localLink:umb://document/41229767036d47f28a27ac846e23458b}" title="Verona">Verona</a> are nice and easy.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 45 mins by coach from Verona airport.</p>]]></description>
